  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  memory complaint, preferably corroborated by a spouse or relative.

          -  objective memory impairment.

          -  normal general cognitive function.

          -  intact activities of daily living.

          -  absence of dementia.

          -  the positive of brain senile plaque.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  more than two lacuna ischemia (of diameter &lt; 1 cm) as revealed by MRI fluid-attenuated
             inversion recovery (FLAIR) sequence.

          -  other type of dementia except AD
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
